1.00	Greatest_Hits_(David_Gray_album)	Greatest Hits (David Gray album)	Greatest Hits is a compilation album by David Gray, released on 12 November 2007 in the UK and a day later in the US. Greatest Hits contains songs from his first album A Century Ends in 1993 through his 2005 album Life in Slow Motion, and includes two new songs: the first single "You're the World to Me" and "Destroyer." In interviews, Gray has described the new single "You're the World to Me" as "joyous" and "unselfconscious," and called his Greatest Hits album: "a bag of happy shit."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/e/e7/David_Gray_Greatest_hits_Album_Cover.jpg
